/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# cargo-fuzz (layer-2, nightly-only) artifacts. The fuzz crate is
# workspace-excluded so it has its own `target/` plus libfuzzer
# outputs that must never land in git.
crates/barbican/fuzz/target/
crates/barbican/fuzz/Cargo.lock
crates/barbican/fuzz/artifacts/
crates/barbican/fuzz/coverage/
# Libfuzzer-discovered inputs are named by their SHA-1 hash: exactly
# 40 lowercase-hex characters with no extension. Our hand-picked seed
# files have descriptive names that always contain at least one `_`
# (`h1_curl_pipe_bash`, `allow_ls`, `ansi_c`, …). Ignoring corpus
# files without an underscore catches libfuzzer-generated entries
# without touching the committed seeds. A future seed file must
# include an underscore to stay tracked.
crates/barbican/fuzz/corpus/**/*
!crates/barbican/fuzz/corpus/
!crates/barbican/fuzz/corpus/*/
!crates/barbican/fuzz/corpus/**/*_*

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Editor scratch
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# OMC state (ephemeral)
.omc/
.claude/

# Cursor-adapt scratch (created by /crew:review when a Cursor reviewer is in
# the roster; removed on cleanup, but we gitignore so a crash doesn't leak)
.cursor/
AGENTS.md
